    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix socket resource leak in E2 agent asio module\n\n### Summary\nThere is a socket resource leak where file descriptors from pipe operations are not properly closed during E2 agent cleanup. This occurs downstream of function `fill_rc_report` in the RAN function setup process.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E2AP/flexric/src/agent/asio_agent.h`: Added `free_asio_agent()` function declaration\n- `openair2/E2AP/flexric/src/agent/asio_agent.c`: Implemented `free_asio_agent()` to properly close pipe file descriptors and epoll fd\n- `openair2/E2AP/flexric/src/agent/e2_agent.c`: Updated `e2_free_agent()` to call `free_asio_agent()` for proper resource cleanup\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Start the E2 agent initialization process which calls `fill_rc_report` as part of RAN function setup\n2. Observe file descriptor leakage using `lsof` or similar tools\n3. After multiple agent initialization/cleanup cycles, the system will eventually exhaust available file descriptors\n4. This manifests as connection failures or \"too many open files\" errors in the E2 communication\n\nThe fix ensures that pipe file descriptors created during `init_asio_agent()` are properly closed when `e2_free_agent()` is called, preventing the resource leak.\n"
}